{
  "text": "The central character defined above is only for even elements in the center of a superalgebra. However, the central character indeed determines the action of odd elements in the center in the following sense: Proposition 2.7. Let z ∈ Z(A) [CITATION_1] . Let X be an irreducible A-supermodule. If X is also an irreducible A-module, then z acts by zero on X. If X is not an irreducible A-module, then z acts on the two irreducible A-submodules of X by two distinct scalars √ λ and − √ λ, where λ is the value that z 2 ∈ Z(A) 0 acts on X.",
